VRES = 0.4                     # vertical resolution
VFOV = (-24.9, 2.0)            # Field of view (-ve, +ve) along vertical axis
Y_FUDGE = 5                    # y fudge factor for velodyne HDL 64E

Sliced channels (8) based on heights¶

In [41]:
im = pcv.projection_birds_eye_multiple_channels(lidar_points, n_slices=6, height_range=(-2.0, 0.27), resolution=0.1)
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15,10), dpi=100)
axes = axes.flatten()
for i,ax in enumerate(axes):
    ax.imshow(im[:,:,i], cmap="gray", vmin=0, vmax=255)
    ax.set_facecolor((0, 0, 0))  
    ax.xaxis.set_visible(False)  
    ax.yaxis.set_visible(False)
    ax.set_title(i, fontdict={"size": 10, "color":"#FFFFFF"})
fig.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.20, hspace=0.20)
fig.show()
#fig.savefig('../images/bird_view_multichannel.png', bbox_inches='tight')

In [13]:
for fn in os.listdir(vlp_streampath):
    with open(os.path.join(vlp_streampath, fn), 'rb') as f:
        d = np.fromfile(f, dtype=np.float32)
        d = d.reshape((int(d.size/4), 4))
        im = pcv.projection_bird_view(d, resolution=0.1, saveto='./point-cloud-images/{}'.format(fn.replace('bin','png')))
